AWS Compute Technologies to Deploy code:
-> EC2 : Deploying virtual machines
-> Elastic Beanstalk : Platform as a service product where you only deploy app and not manage underlying infrastructure
-> Lambda : Deploying only stateless functions
-> EC2 Container Service : Allows you to manage Docker clusters

Amazon EC2
-> You select a machine image (could be linux, windows etc.)
-> You select instance size
-> You start your virtual machine
-> Once the server is up, you can connect to it, just like any other server
-> You get load balancing, monitoring, auto-scaling, network storage